For portability, it's nice to use `boost::filesystem` with the `/` operator instead of using "/" characters. See [examples_build.cc](#!/osrf/gazebo/src/5b7f3c2a02db5310b167675b018cce53341ca806/test/examples/examples_build.cc?at=default#cl-40) for an example.

~~~
  boost::filesystem::path filePath = std::string(PROJECT_SOURCE_PATH);
  path /= std::string("test");
  path /= std::string("data");
  path /= std::string("svg");
  path /= std::string("arc_circle.svg");
~~~
